Package eu.h2020.helios_social.core.contextualegonetwork

Class CrossModuleComponent

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.h2020.helios_social.core.contextualegonetwork.CrossModuleComponent
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Context, Edge, Node
    public abstract class CrossModuleComponent
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a base class used by HELIOS components, such as Node and Edge that need to store data coming from multiple modules. The getOrCreateInstance(java.lang.Class<ModuleObjectDataType>) method can be used to create and access instances of data structures needed by each module.
    Author:
    Emmanouil Krasanakis (maniospas@iti.gr)

      • getOrCreateInstance

        public <ModuleObjectDataType> ModuleObjectDataType getOrCreateInstance​(java.lang.String moduleName,
                                                                       java.lang.Class<ModuleObjectDataType> moduleClass)
        Retrieves an instance of the given class that is stored in the component. If no such instance exists, a new one is created first using either a constructor with this object as an argument or a default constructor (i.e. a constructor with no argument). Both classes to be created and constructors need be of public visibility. The default constructor assumes lower priority.

        Remarks

        - Refrain from directly referencing other CrossModuleComponent objects (the one creating the instance is fine), as these could be removed from the contextual ego network and keeping references to them can induce unexpected behavior.
        - Created instances are saved and loaded alongside nodes if these are part of a contextual ego network structure. Notably, if more than one created instances -for example of the same class with different module names- comprise references to the same object but the latter not registered in the Serializer, two separate instances of that object would be created upon loading the contextual ego network.
        - If modifications of created instances occur, these do not trigger any listener callbacks of the contextual ego network. For example, this means that changes to the created instances are not saved by RecoveryListener.
        Type Parameters:
        ModuleObjectDataType - The implicitly understood type of the returned object (is automatically resolved to the same as the type of the given class)
        Parameters:
        moduleName - A custom name to reference the class instance by future calls of this method.
        moduleClass - The given class (e.g. that stores the node's data needed by a HELIOS module).
        Returns:
        An instance of the given class unique to the given module name.

      • getOrCreateInstance

        public <ModuleObjectDataType> ModuleObjectDataType getOrCreateInstance​(java.lang.String moduleName,
                                                                       java.util.function.Supplier<ModuleObjectDataType> moduleClassSupplier)
        A variation of getOrCreateInstance(String, Class) that takes a supplier returning objects of the inferred class instead of automatically determining the constructor. Similarly to the original functionality, if the object is already there it. The supplier pattern is used to avoid passing instantiated objects that are never stored.
        Make sure that the supplier returns a different instance each time.
        Type Parameters:
        ModuleObjectDataType - The implicitly understood type of the returned object (is automatically resolved to the same as the type of the given class)
        Parameters:
        moduleName - A custom name to reference the class instance by future calls of this method.
        moduleClassSupplier - The method returning the instance.
        Returns:
        An instance of the given class.
